.TH erl_expand_records 3 "stdlib 7.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
erl_expand_records \- This module expands records in a module.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBSee Also\fR

.PP
Section The Abstract Format in ERTS User's Guide.

.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBmodule(AbsForms, CompileOptions) -> AbsForms2\fR
\fB                when\fR
\fB                    AbsForms :: [erl_parse:abstract_form()],\fR
\fB                    AbsForms2 :: [erl_parse:abstract_form()],\fR
\fB                    CompileOptions :: [compile:option()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Expands all records in a module to use explicit tuple operations and adds explicit module names to calls to BIFs and imported functions. The returned module has no references to records, attributes, or code.


.RE
